==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Morin
<hw>Mo"rin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A
yellow crystalline substance (<chform>C15H10O7</chform>) of acid
properties extracted from <prodby>fustic</prodby> (<spn>Chlorophora
tinctoria</spn> syn. <spn>Maclura tinctoria</spn>, formerly called
<altname>Morus tinctoria</altname>); -- called also <altname>moric
acid</altname> and <altname>natural yellow 8</altname>. It is used as a
dye for wool, giving a color from lemon yellow through olive to olive
brown, depending on the metal with which it is mordanted.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Morinda</ent>⟦br⟧
